clinicalDescription: Overview: is a pathological diagnosis of atherosclerotic changes in the coronary blood vessels. Presentation: The prevalence of coronary arteriosclerosis in population is almost 100%, with only a small number of individuals having symptomatic areteriosclerosis (ischemia). Assessment: evaluation is usually done after the first symptom suspected to be due to coronary vascular disease. Plan: risk factor management such as lipid management. Prognosis: may be managed with life style modfication or pharmacological interventions.
